        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-16T20:52:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is subscribeAsync ok with the possibility of its callback blocking?  At the moment, I notice commitCh is unbuffered, so if two commits come in in close succession, line 240 will block.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 239,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 239,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "cb6d49fa3767b734ca804dfdeabdd4fd8e76ae50",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6f98dbe0_3b5e306b",
        "filename": "golden/go/indexer/indexer.go",
        "patchSetId": 28
      },
      "lineNbr": 239,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-17T18:22:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The function that is passed to SubscribeAsync is always called on it\u0027s own go-routine when the corresponding event is published. \nI made both channels (commitCh and expCh) buffered with plenty of room. I don\u0027t think it will make a huge difference, but there are edge cases where it could increase throughput significantly and the buffer size (100) is negligible.",
      "parentUuid": "2c226ea3_d22d0248",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 239,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 239,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "cb6d49fa3767b734ca804dfdeabdd4fd8e76ae50",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8589d5fd_52da752a",
        "filename": "golden/go/indexer/indexer.go",
        "patchSetId": 28
      },
      "lineNbr": 271,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-16T20:52:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t know if I\u0027ve ever seen this idiom before.  Why not do a for tn :\u003d range expCh ?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 271,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 271,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "cb6d49fa3767b734ca804dfdeabdd4fd8e76ae50",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bf292469_7945d66d",
        "filename": "golden/go/indexer/indexer.go",
        "patchSetId": 28
      },
      "lineNbr": 271,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-17T18:22:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Because when doing \u0027for x :\u003d range ch\u0027 the channel has to be closed for the loop to end.\nHere I only want to read what\u0027s immediately in the channel and available for reading. \nIf nothing is left in the channel we leave the loop. \nIt\u0027s designed to drain the channel but only to the point of what I can get right now. \nAdded documentation about why drain the channels (also added draining the commitCh channel).\n\nReplace the boolean with a break statement.",
      "parentUuid": "8589d5fd_52da752a",
      "range": {
